Run the following chuck if you want just NE cells doublets included

Run the following chuck if you want just NE cells doublets excluded

Run the following chuck if you want ALL cells (+additional datasets) cells doublets excluded Load data

data_adult <- read.table(paste(dir,"input/GC_table_ALL_datasets.tsv",sep=""))
meta_adult_new <- read.table(paste(dir,"input/Metadata_ALL_datasets.tsv",sep=""))

Create Seurat object of whichever dataset you decided to use

require(Seurat)
tiss <- CreateSeuratObject(raw.data = data_adult, project = "NE_Lung", meta.data = meta_adult_new, 
                           display.progress = T)
tiss <- AddMetaData(object = tiss, metadata = meta_adult_new)
# save(tiss, file = paste(dir,"input/NE_Lung_Seurat.RData",sep=""))

Filter the dataset and preprocess Filtering on 1000 genes minimum and 50000 reads minimum per cell

tiss <- FilterCells(object = tiss, subset.names = c("nGene", "nUMI"), 
    low.thresholds = c(1000, 50000), high.thresholds = c(Inf, Inf))
tiss
## An object of class seurat in project NE_Lung 
##  23316 genes across 2727 samples.

Preprocess data

tiss <- NormalizeData(object = tiss, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", 
    scale.factor = 1000000)
tiss <- ScaleData(object = tiss, do.scale = T, do.center = T)
## Scaling data matrix

Find variable genes

tiss <- FindVariableGenes(object = tiss, do.plot = TRUE, x.high.cutoff = Inf, y.cutoff = 1, num.bin = 20, 
                                          binning.method = "equal_width", do.recalc = T, x.low.cutoff=1)

Perform PCA

tiss <- RunPCA(object = tiss, do.print = FALSE)
tiss <- ProjectPCA(object = tiss, do.print = FALSE)

Visualize top genes across principal components

PCHeatmap(object = tiss, pc.use = 1:15, cells.use = 100, do.balanced = TRUE, label.columns = FALSE, num.genes = 10)

Perform correlation of PCs and metadata fields

pca.obj <- tiss@dr$pca
pc.coords <- pca.obj@cell.embeddings
df1 <- tiss@meta.data[,c("nGene","nUMI")]
df2 <- pc.coords[,c(1:10)]
cordf12 <- cor(df1,df2)
# Make a correlation plot
corrplot(cordf12, method = "number", main="Correlation of PCs and metadata")

Also visaulize PC variance

#comp.dev <-pca.obj@sdev
PCElbowPlot(object = tiss)

Plot a few of the principal components

temp <- tiss@dr$pca@cell.embeddings
temp <- as.data.frame(temp)
names <- colnames(temp)
temp <- cbind(temp, tiss@meta.data$dataset)
colnames(temp) <- c(names, "dataset")
pca.scatter = ggpairs(data=temp,
             columns=1:10, 
             upper = list(continuous = "points"),
             lower = list(combo = "na"),
             mapping=ggplot2::aes(colour = dataset), legend = 2) + theme(legend.position = "bottom")
ggsave(plot = pca.scatter, filename = "~/Documents/Labwork/Projects/Biohub/NE_Lung/plot_out/NE04/PCA_scatterplots_largefile.pdf",width = 15, height = 12)

Choose the number of principal components to use.

n.pcs = 10

Set resolution and perform clustering

res.used <- 0.3
tiss <- FindClusters(object = tiss, reduction.type = "pca", dims.use = 1:n.pcs, 
    resolution = res.used, print.output = 0, save.SNN = TRUE, k.param = 5)

Perform tSNE

set.seed(123)
tiss <- RunTSNE(object = tiss, dims.use = 1:n.pcs, seed.use = 10, perplexity=30)

Visualize TSNE colored by cluster

TSNEPlot(object = tiss, do.label = T)

Plot the fraction of each dataset in each

tab.1 <- table(tiss@meta.data$dataset,tiss@meta.data$res.0.3)
balloonplot(tab.1)

Color by a gene. Feature plot

FeaturePlot(tiss, c("Ascl1", "Epcam", "zsGreen_transgene"))

Color by a gene. Dot plot

DotPlot(tiss, c("Ascl1", "Epcam", "zsGreen_transgene"))

Visualize TSNE metadata field Experiment ID

# note that you can set do.label=T to help label individual clusters
TSNEPlot(object = tiss, do.label = F, group.by = "dataset")

Save object

save(tiss,file=paste(dir,"input/All_datasets_ND.RData",sep=""))
